  "text": "The changing health state of gear teeth can lead to variations of amplitude and phase modulations of the meshing vibrations. As such, a trend analysis on the intensity of the modulation components can be effectively used to track the health state of gear pairs [CITATION_1] . To verify the effectiveness of the proposed method, as well as that of the neural network structure for fault diagnosis applications, simulated gear crack fault signals are established as below.",
